<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Chocolatey package metadata for Surgewave.

  The version + checksum get patched in by the release pipeline
  (.github/workflows/chocolatey.yml) before `choco pack` runs:
    - <version> is replaced with the SemVer string for the tag
      (e.g. 0.1.0)
    - tools/chocolateyInstall.ps1 has the SHA256 of the corresponding
      MSI baked in for chocolatey-side download verification.

  Chocolatey community-feed submission goes through a moderation
  queue — first submission for a new package can take 1-7 days, later
  versions usually pass within hours. The pipeline runs `choco push`
  on every stable tag; the moderation step is async on the chocolatey
  side and not blocking the rest of the release.
-->
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>surgewave</id>
    <version>__VERSION__</version>
    <packageSourceUrl>https://github.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave/tree/main/packaging/chocolatey</packageSourceUrl>
    <owners>Kuestenlogik</owners>

    <title>Surgewave</title>
    <authors>Kuestenlogik</authors>
    <projectUrl>https://surgewave.io/</projectUrl>
    <iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave/main/site/assets/images/mark_adaptive.svg</iconUrl>
    <copyright>Copyright (c) Küstenlogik</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave/blob/main/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave</projectSourceUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://surgewave.io/docs/</docsUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <tags>surgewave kafka message-broker event-streaming dotnet aspnet schema-registry connect mqtt amqp websocket</tags>
    <summary>The .NET-native message streaming platform — Kafka-wire-compatible broker, Control UI, CLI. Drop-in replacement for Apache Kafka with built-in AI pipelines, schemas, and a plugin marketplace.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
**Surgewave** is the .NET-native message streaming platform.
Wire-compatible with Apache Kafka 4.0 (any existing Kafka client connects
on day one), with built-in AI pipeline nodes, a Confluent-compatible Schema
Registry, 100+ connectors, and an embedded mode for tests and edge.

Run it embedded inside your .NET app, as a standalone broker, or scaled
out across a cluster. Pure .NET 10 — no JVM, no ZooKeeper, single
technology stack.

This package installs the **Surgewave Broker**, **Control UI**, and
**`surgewave` CLI** on Windows x64. The MSI registers the broker as a
Windows service, adds the CLI directory to system PATH, and drops Start
Menu shortcuts for the Control UI dashboard.

**Quick start after install:**

```powershell
# Start the broker service
Start-Service SurgewaveBroker

# Connect from any Kafka client
$config = New-Object Confluent.Kafka.ProducerConfig
$config.BootstrapServers = "localhost:9092"

# Open the Control UI
Start-Process http://localhost:5050
```

See [https://surgewave.io](https://surgewave.io) for documentation,
samples, and the open-source repository.

**License:** Apache 2.0 (core). Premium extensions ship in separate
repositories under the Business Source License 1.1.
]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/Kuestenlogik/Surgewave/releases/tag/v__VERSION__</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools/**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
